  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>Defined by the equation a = e((µ - µo)/RT) where R is the gas constant, T the thermodynamic temperature, µ the chemical potential and µ0 the standard chemical potential the definition of which depends on the choice of the standard state.</text>
